# for-comprehensions on `List`

R.2.5 lowers `for x <- xs yield expr` (single-generator) to
Rust `xs.into_iter().map(|x| expr).collect::<Vec<_>>()`, plus
`List(...)` ctor to `vec![...]` and `List[T]` type to `Vec<T>`.

```scalascript
def doubled(xs: List[Long]): List[Long] =
  for x <- xs yield x * 2

@main def run(): Unit =
  val ys: List[Long] = doubled(List(1, 2, 3, 4))
  println(ys.size)
```

Build and run:

```bash
ssc build-rust for-yield.ssc
./for-yield                  # → 4
```
